Just as the Obafemi Awolowo University, Ile-Ife and the general public await the outcome of the report of the investigative panel that was constituted to investigate alleged sexual harassment by a lecturer of the institution, another teacher of the University was yesterday suspended over sexually molesting a 19-year-old female student. Recall that the panel set up to look into the allegations of sexual harassment against Mr Olabisi Olaleye, a lecturer in the Department of International Relations submitted its reports to the vice chancellor of the university, Professor Eyitope Ogunbodede few weeks ago. Ogunbodede while receiving the report had urged any student or member of the university community to avail themselves of the opportunity of the open door policy of his administration to report any infringement on their rights by anybody to the appropriate organ of the university for possible investigation and redress. However, less than three weeks after the Management of the institution expressed her zero tolerance against the act by investigating Olabisi Olaleye, the axe of the university has fallen on another worker. A release made available to newsmen in Osogbo yesterday by the public relations officer of the university, Abiodun Olarewaju, stated that  the university had also handed over the tutor, Mr Monday Omo – Etan, of the school of Distance Learning of the institution to the police.  